HEADWORD: Asthma
<hw>Asth"ma</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
short-drawn breath, fr. <?/ to blow, for <?/: cf. Skr.
<ets>v⟦amac⟧</ets>, Goth. <ets>waian</ets>, to blow, E.
<ets>wind</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease, characterized
by difficulty of breathing (due to a spasmodic contraction of the
bronchi), recurring at intervals, accompanied with a wheezing sound, a
sense of constriction in the chest, a cough, and
expectoration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

